[h1] Webrings

[p-]
A webring connects your page to a curated list of other podweb pages.
Visitors can browse all member pages using previous and next buttons
embedded right on your page.
[-p]

[h2] Adding the widget to your page

[code-]
[webring my-url=podnet://YOUR_ID/index.podweb, ring-data=podnet://48932/first.webring]
[-code]

[p-]
Set my-url to the full podnet URL of the page where the widget appears.
Set ring-data to the URL of the webring file.
The widget shows the ring title, a join link, and previous/next buttons.
[-p]

[p-]
If your URL is not in the ring yet the buttons navigate from a random
position until the ring owner adds you.
[-p]

[h2] The webring file format

[p] A webring is a plain text file on podnet:

[code-]
<ring title>
<url to the join page>
<url of member 1>
<url of member 2>
...
[-code]

[p-]
The first line is the display title. The second line is a page where
visitors can learn how to contact you to join. Every following line is
a member URL.
[-p]

[h2] Example

[code-]
the first webring
podnet://48932/join-webring.podweb
podnet://48932/index.podweb
podnet://78402/index.podweb
podnet://135230/index.podweb
[-code]

